50|$|Gul Rahman was {{captured}} and arrested on 29 October 2002 during a joint operation by U.S. agents and Pakistani security forces against <b>Hezb-e-Islami</b> Gulbuddin. He was reportedly arrested with the physician Ghairat Baheer, the son-in-law of the warlord Gulbuddin Hekmatyar, {{who leads the}} insurgent faction <b>Hezb-e-Islami.</b> Rahman had traveled from Peshawar to Islamabad, Pakistan for a medical checkup {{when he was arrested}} at the home of Ghairat Baheer, and subsequently flown by the CIA to Afghanistan.|$|E
